CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Election Law – Campaign Finance Entities – Oversight and Control of Campaign
3 Funds
4 FOR the purpose of altering the manner in which a campaign manager may be appointed;
5 requiring the candidate to appoint the chair and treasurer of an authorized candidate
6 campaign committee; repealing the requirement that a campaign manager be a
7 registered voter of the State; altering the offices that a candidate is prohibited from
8 holding in a campaign; providing that the treasurer is the financial steward of a
9 campaign finance entity; altering requirements for assets received by or on behalf of
10 a campaign finance entity and disbursements made by or on behalf of a campaign
11 finance entity; repealing the authority of the chair of a campaign finance entity to
12 approve a disbursement on behalf of the campaign finance entity under certain
13 circumstances; authorizing the treasurer a candidate or the responsible officers of a
14 campaign finance entity to designate authorized agents to make disbursements carry
