2 SENATE BILL 153
1 out duties on behalf of the campaign finance entity; prohibiting a candidate from
2 having access to, or making a disbursement from, campaign funds in the designated
3 campaign account; requiring a candidate to have knowledge of all disbursements
4 made from the designated campaign account of the candidate’s authorized candidate
5 campaign committee; and generally relating to campaign finance entities and
6 oversight and control of campaign funds.
7 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
8 Article – Election Law
9 Section 1–101(a), 13–248, and 13–604.1(f) 13–604.1(d) and (f)
